CHANGELOG:
03-14-2013: Added Support of LUN in Master/Slave
	    Added possibity to run in infiniband mode only, iscsi only, or both ib and iscsi.
            Various bug corrections.
	    Changed parameter lun to iscsi_lun, for different lun handling by different drivers (for example ib).
03-06-2013: Added Infiniband (SRP) support.
04-31-2012: Modified LUN stop behavior, the session with initiator is 
            closed only if initiator is connected to LUN the script is
            stopping.

INSTALLATION

Place files SCSTTarget and SCSTLun into pacemaker ocf directory (usually 
/usr/lib/ocf/resource.d or /usr/lib64/ocf/resource.d)

EXAMPLE OF USAGE

Assumptions: 
- you are using DRBD as backing device (/dev/drbd1)
- your target iqn is iqn.2012-02.com.mysuperhasan:vdisk.lun
- your nic reserved for iscsi is eth2 and your iscsi subnet is 192.168.103.x

This is what your resource configuration in cib notation will look like:


primitive DRBD_VOLUME ocf:linbit:drbd \
	params drbd_resource="DRBDRESOURCE" \
	op monitor interval="29" role="Master" \
	op monitor interval="31" role="Slave"
primitive ISCSI_IP ocf:heartbeat:IPaddr2 \
	params ip="192.168.103.20" cidr_netmask="24" nic="eth2" \
	op monitor interval="10s"
primitive ISCSI_LUN ocf:scst:SCSTLun \
	params iscsi_enable="1" target_iqn="iqn.2012-02.com.mysuperhasan:vdisk.lun" iscsi_lun="0" \
	path="/dev/drbd1" handler="vdisk_fileio" device_name="VDISK-LUN10" \ 		
	additional_parameters="nv_cache=1" \
	op monitor interval="10s" timeout="120s"
primitive ISCSI_TGT ocf:scst:SCSTTarget \
	params iscsi_enable="1" iqn="iqn.2012-02.com.mysuperhasan:vdisk.lun" \
	portals="192.168.103.20" \
	op monitor interval="10s" timeout="120s"
group GR_ISCSI ISCSI_TGT ISCSI_LUN ISCSI_IP
ms MS_DRBD_VOLUME DRBD_VOLUME \
	meta master-max="1" master-node-max="1" clone-max="2" \
	clone-node-max="1" notify="true"
colocation CO_ISCSI_ON_DRBD_VOLUME inf: GR_ISCSI MS_DRBD_VOLUME:Master
order OR_DRBD_BEFORE_ISCSI inf: MS_DRBD_VOLUME:promote GR_ISCSI:start


INFINIBAND:
For now infiniband support is using one target per HCA model, with SCST auto-created target names.
Soon it will be ported in one target per per mode, with target names represented by HCA port GUID 

The CIB for infiniband looks like this:

primitive ISCSI_LUN ocf:scst:SCSTLun \
	params target_iqn="iqn.2012-02.com.mysuperhasan:vdisk.lun" lun="0" \
	path="/dev/drbd1" handler="vdisk_fileio" device_name="VDISK-LUN10" \ 		
	srpt_enable=1 additional_parameters="nv_cache=1" \
	op monitor interval="10s" timeout="120s"
primitive ISCSI_TGT ocf:scst:SCSTTarget \
	params iqn="iqn.2012-02.com.mysuperhasan:vdisk.lun" \
	portals="192.168.103.20" \
	srpt_enable=1 \
	op monitor interval="10s" timeout="120s"

MASTER/SLAVE LUN:
I added preliminary support for Master/Slave LUN. For now it only works with iSCSI.
After testing it will be released a version with infiniband support.

The SCSTLunMS Resource Agent is intended to be used on a resource stack like this:

+ SCST ISCSI TARGET (Cloned Resource)
  + SCST LUN Master
  + DRBD Resource Master

When LUN is running as Master,  is pointing to a "real device", when running slave is pointing to a NULLIO
device.


A testing CIB will look like:

primitive ISCSI_TGT ocf:scst:SCSTTarget \
	params iqn="iqn.2012-02.com.mysuperhasan:vdisk.lun" \
	portals="192.168.103.20 192.168.104.20" \
	op monitor interval="10s" timeout="120s" 
clone CL_ISCSI_TGT ISCSI_TGT \
        clone-max="2" clone-node-max="1"
primitive DUMMY_LUN0 ocf:heartbeat:Dummy \
        op monitor interval="10s"
primitive ISCSI_LUN0 ocf:scst:SCSTLunMS \
        params target_iqn="iqn.2012-02.com.mysuperhasan:vdisk.lun" lun="0" path="/dev/drbd1" handler="vdisk_fileio" device_name="VDISK-LUN0" scsi_id="LUN00" scsi_sn="000010" additional_parameters="nv_cache=1" \
        op monitor interval="10s" timeout="120s"
ms MS_ISCSI_LUN0 ISCSI_LUN0 \
        meta master-max="1" master-node-max="1" clone-max="2" clone-node-max="1" notify="true"
colocation CO_LUN0 inf: DUMMY_LUN0 MS_ISCSI_LUN0:Master
colocation CO_LUN0_ON_DRBD inf: MS_ISCSI_LUN0:Master MS_DRBD_VOLUME:Master
order OR_LUN0 inf: MS_DRBD_VOLUME:promote MS_ISCSI_LUN0:promote

Please note that parameter names are in "old style" (no iscsi_enable, no srpt_enable, no iscsi_lun)

CURRENT LIMITATIONS

Scripts are tested only with straight drbd or lvm over drbd as backing device, 
using vdisk_fileio, with one lun per target.

CHAP authentication is configurable, but not yet tested. My current version of SCST
throws an error while adding chap parameters.

